public interface Proxy

The interface for light-weight singleton classes that listens for events before the full Presenter is instantiated. This include, among others, the presenter's specific SetContentEvent that needs the presenter to reveal itself.

The relationship between a presenter and its proxy is two-way.

This class is called PresenterProxy instead of simply Proxy because Presenter subclasses will usually define their own interface called Proxy and derived from this one. Naming this interface Proxy would therefore be impractical for code-writing purposes.

Author:
beaudoin
